5. Optional native library: PDFium
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

CPSL can optionally load Google PDFium for PDF features via the
pdfium-render crate and platform binaries (see core/scripts/download-pdfium.sh).

  - pdfium-render (Rust crate): Apache-2.0 OR MIT
    https://github.com/ajrcarey/pdfium-render
  - PDFium native library: typically obtained from
    https://github.com/bblanchon/pdfium-binaries
    PDFium (Chromium) is licensed under a BSD-style license; see the
    LICENSE files shipped with the PDFium binary package you redistribute.
    Do not redistribute PDFium binaries without including their upstream
    license and copyright notices.

PDFium is not always present in every CPSL build. Include PDFium notices
whenever you ship libpdfium / pdfium shared libraries alongside CPSL.

